"{\"uid\": \"thesouthafrican.com-lifestyle-celeb-news-international-celebs-olympics-opening-ceremony-elon-musk-andrew-tate-latest\", \"text\": \"Copyright Blue Sky Publications (Pty) Ltd. All Rights Reserved.  thesouthafrican.com is a division of Blue Sky Publications Ltd. Reproduction without permission prohibited  Home\\u00bbElon Musk calls for Christians to 'stand up' against Olympics show  Elon Musk has called on Christians to be 'brave to stand up for what is fair and right', amid the Olympics Opening Ceremony scandal.  The world's richest man, Elon Musk, is one of the biggest and loudest critics of the Paris\\u00a0Olympics Opening Ceremony, which he believes was \\\"disrespectful to all Christians.\\\"  Musk - who was born in Pretoria, South Africa - has also chastised Christians for allowing their faith to be publicly desecrated at the global sporting event.  The performance has beencriticised for parodying the Last Supper painting,which represents Jesus and his 12 disciples.  On his official account, the X founder criticised the Paris Olympics Opening Ceremony on Friday, 26 July.  \\\"This was extremely disrespectful to Christians,\\\" he tweeted.  The businessman also retweeted messages claiming that the Olympics woulddare not insult other religions.  When one tweep posted a side-by-side of The Last Supper and the Opening Ceremony with the words: \\\"Doing this results in fewer dead people than if the imagery of Islam was mocked,\\\" Elon responded: \\\"Christianity has become toothless.\\\"  He added in another tweet: \\\"Unless there is more bravery to stand up for what is fair and right, Christianity will perish.\\\"  When on tweep questioned about his religious standing, Elon Musk responded: \\\"I believe in the principles of Christianity like love thy neighbor as thyself (have empathy for all) and turn the other cheek (end the cycle of retribution)\\\".  Meanwhile, outspoken social media personality Andrew Tate has also condemned the visuals of the Olympics Opening Ceremony.  He's even gone as far as to call on others to boycott the global sporting event.  In a video post, he added, \\\"The worst part is that none of this has anything to do with sports. They could've done this at any other time, but no, they chose this random event\\\".  Andrew - who is based in Romania -\\u00a0 also posted a clip of him protesting outside the French embassy.  He tweeted: \\\"I am protesting outside of the French embassy for mocking Jesus during the Olympics ceremony.  \\\"The police are threatening to arrest me for unlawful assembly. I am currently on bail and will face a minimum of three months in prison. I do this as a Muslim\\\".  He added: \\\"WHERE ARE THE CHRISTIANS?\\\"    'The South African' is hiring! Freelance writer positions available. Send us your CV  The draw for Rugby World Cup 2027 will take place in Sydney, Australia on Wednesday, 3 December at 11:00 (SA time).  Today's Daily Lotto jackpot stands at an estimated R550 000. If you want to win your share of the jackpot, you have to play!  Faberge's The Winter Egg, fetched a record \\u00a322.9 million (R518 million) at auction on Tuesday, Christie's said.  Former Pirates star Phumudzo Manenzhe has discussed the exclusion of Thapelo Morena from Bafana Bafana's AFCON 2025 squad.  Kaizer Chiefs will play their penultimate match of 2025 on Wednesday, 3 December when they visit Chippa United in Gqeberha.  Secures a NEW shopping bag? Woolworths has seemingly disassociated itself with the testimony of 'tenderpreneur' Vusi 'Cat Matlala\\u2026    TheSouthAfrican.com is all about South Africa and the stories that affect South Africans, wherever they are in the world.  We are independent.No agenda.No bias.  Our offices are for administrative purposes only, no visitors will be accepted without an appointment.  South Africa- Blue Sky Publications (Pty) Ltd - Registration Number: 2005/028472/07 - Address: Regus Business Centre, 1st Floor, Block B, North Park, Black River Park, 2 